<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-603-899  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 603 899.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  Nov 5 1990 v7 n13 p104(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Textware 3.0 cuts information overload. (indexing and retrievalsystem facilitates locating text-based data) (Software Review)(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bowden, Eric J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Textware 3.0 is a user-friendly free-text indexing and retrievalsystem from Textware Corp that is priced at $495 for a standaloneversion or $2,995 for a networked package.andP;  Installation is simpleand straightforward.andP;  Textware allows the user to organize wordprocessing and ASCII files into pieces of data of virtually anysize called 'Cards', which are in turn organized into 'Cardfiles',which can contain any number of cards.andP;  Information is retrievedfrom the Cardfiles by entering keywords at the search prompt.andO;Textware creates a 'Hits List' of all cards containing thekeyword, from which the user can select and view the completetext.andP;  The package's user's manual and documentation are includedas a sample Cardfile and access to the online documentation is farsuperior to a standard manual.andP;  CardFiles can be subdivided intodocuments according to user-specified parameters, speeding thesearch process.andP;  Documents can be stored in native mode, best forfrequently modified files, or in Textware's internal format fordata that is essentially static.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Textware Corp. (Products).andO;Product:   Textware 3.0 (Utility program).andO;Topic:     EvaluationDocument Management SystemsInformation Storage and RetrievalIndexing.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   How the CardFile concept works. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>